{{$NEXT}}
    [New Features]
    - Add ShellSort algorithm using Ciura's empirically optimal gap sequence
    - Add QuickSelect via qselect() API — find kth smallest element in O(n) average
    - Add string variant quick_select_str() for lexicographic selection

    [Bug Fixes]
    - Fix undefined behavior on empty arrays (HeapSort read out of bounds, Newx(0))
    - Fix memory leak on croak() — validate inputs before allocating output SVs
    - Fix integer overflow in midpoint calculation: use Left+(Right-Left)/2
    - Fix silent fallback bug in xsort(): use // instead of || for parameter merging
    - Fix MergeSort to use Newx/Safefree instead of raw malloc/free
    - Remove dead compiler defines (ARCH_IS_BIG_ENDIAN, WINDOWS) from build config
    - Remove spurious FindBin dependency from cpanfile
    - Fix broken reverse-range test cases (Perl's [42..24] is empty, not reversed)

    [Performance]
    - QuickSort: raise insertion sort cutoff from 3 to 16, add tail-call optimization
    - HeapSort: Floyd's bottom-up sift reduces comparisons by ~50%
    - ShellSort: Ciura's gap sequence replaces Shell's original N/2 sequence
    - Data marshalling: use AvARRAY() direct access, av_extend() pre-allocation
    - Integer comparison: branchless (a>b)-(a<b) replaces ternary
    - MergeSort copy-back: memcpy replaces per-element loop

    [Testing]
    - Add comprehensive adversarial sort test suite (pre-sorted, reverse, all-equal,
      pipe-organ, sawtooth, Dutch flag, extreme IV values, size boundaries)
    - Add empty array edge case tests
    - Add corner case tests with IV_MIN/IV_MAX values

    [Distribution]
    - Switch to Dist::Zilla for distribution management
    - Generate README.md from POD
    - Version from git tags via Git::NextVersion
    - Add CLAUDE.md project development guide
    - Add GitHub Actions CI (Linux multi-Perl, macOS, Windows)

